14 SECTION 2.(d) G.S. 58-19-40 reads as rewritten:
15 "§ 58-19-40. Confidential treatment.
16 (a) Documents, materials, or other information in the possession or control of the
17 Department that are obtained by or disclosed to the Commissioner or any other person in the
18 course of an examination or investigation made pursuant to G.S. 58-19-35, and all information
19 reported or provided to the Department pursuant to subdivisions (11a) and (11b) of
20 G.S. 58-19-15(b), G.S. 58-19-25, G.S. 58-19-30 and G.S. 58-19-38 are recognized by this State
21 as being proprietary and to contain trade secrets, and shall be confidential by law and privileged,
22 shall not be considered a public record under either G.S. 58-2-100 or Chapter 132 of the General
23 Statutes, shall not be subject to subpoena, and shall not be subject to discovery or admissible in
24 evidence in any private civil action. However, the Commissioner is authorized to use the
25 documents, materials, or other information in the furtherance of any regulatory or legal action
26 brought as a part of the Commissioner's official duties. The Commissioner shall not otherwise
27 make the documents, materials, or other information public without the prior written consent of
28 the insurer to which it pertains unless the Commissioner, after giving the insurer and its affiliates
29 who would be affected thereby notice and opportunity to be heard, determines that the interest of
30 policyholders, shareholders, or the public will be served by the publication thereof, in which
31 event the Commissioner may publish all or any part of the information in such manner as may
32 be deemed appropriate.
33 (a1) With respect to information provided to the Department pursuant to G.S. 58-19-26
